<h2 id="semantic-markup-with-sass">Semantic Markup With Sass</h2>
<p>You can create your own forms using our Sass mixins.</p>
<h3>Pre/Postfix Mixin</h3>

<p>You can use the <code>prefix-postfix-base()</code> and <code>prefix()</code> mixin to create your own form, like so:</p>
<h5 id="base-mixin">Base mixin</h5>
<div class="row">
  <div class="large-6 columns">
    <h4>SCSS</h4>
<pre><code class="language-scss"><div class="code-container"><span class="class">.custom-prefix-class</span> {
  <span class="at_rule">@<span class="keyword">include</span><span class="preprocessor"> prefix-postfix-base</span>();</span>
  <span class="at_rule">@<span class="keyword">include</span><span class="preprocessor"> grid-column</span>(
    $columns:<span class="number">3</span>,
    $float:left
  );</span>
}

<span class="tag">input</span><span class="attr_selector">[type="text"]</span><span class="class">.custom-input-class</span> {
  <span class="at_rule">@<span class="keyword">include</span><span class="preprocessor"> grid-column</span>($columns:<span class="number">9</span>);</span>
}</div></code></pre>

  </div>
  <div class="large-6 columns">
<pre><code class="language-html"><div class="code-container"><span class="tag">&lt;<span class="title">form</span>&gt;</span>
